        <mxCell id="4YRg_xzSH1VSa469GJhv-35" value="&lt;b&gt;ProtoProxy&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Protoproxy watch keys in protobuf buckets in nats.&lt;br&gt;For each pb, it create a routine that liscen to the tlm stream. The subject contain the package name of of the proto.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can start protoproxy with a specific key, a set of keys, or all&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Alernatives could be to have the package name part of the header or the message name part of the stream subject. This change the granualarity.&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;darkOpacity=0.05;align=left;verticalAlign=top;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-710" y="1260" width="271" height="200" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4YRg_xzSH1VSa469GJhv-37" value="&lt;b&gt;ProtoCommand&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Part of device boot is to send the name of the proto package link to the device, so we then can make the mapping. This allow command discovery per device.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Else, work similar to protoproxy&lt;div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;darkOpacity=0.05;align=left;verticalAlign=top;" parent="1" vertex="1">
